Genitalia
. Pygophore brown, elongate setae generally scattered and with a dense brush posteriorly (Fig. 
2
). Parameres lacking. Phallosoma with basal oblique striations hidden behind pygophore; abrupt ventrodextral gibbosity; shaft extending obliquely to left to apex; apex bluntly pointed, with left side appearing flattened in dorsal view but actually open as broad, longitudinal channel in view from left, ventral side of channel lightly sclerotized and narrowly rounded, dorsal rim carinate (Fig. 
2
); sclerotized vesica distad of phallosoma.
